the school was founded by walter gropius in weimar in 1919, as a merger of the weimar saxon grand ducal art school and the weimar academy of fine art . 
the school's philosophy stated that the artist should be trained to work with the industry . 
the school closed in 1968, but the `` ulm model '' concept continues to influence international design education . 
when it gained control of the dessau city council ,  it moved to close the school . 
the physical plant at dessau survived world war ii and was operated as a design school with some architectural facilities by the german democratic republic . 
the staatliches bauhaus  -lrb-    -rrb-  ,  commonly known as the bauhaus ,  was a german art school operational from 1919 to 1933 that combined crafts and the fine arts ,  and was famous for the approach to design that it publicized and taught . 
for example ,  the pottery shop was discontinued when the school moved from weimar to dessau ,  even though it had been an important revenue source; when mies van der rohe took over the school in 1930, he transformed it into a private school ,  and would not allow any supporters of hannes meyer to attend it . 
the bauhaus had a profound influence upon subsequent developments in art ,  architecture ,  graphic design ,  interior design ,  industrial design ,  and typography . 
victor vasarely ,  a pioneer of op art ,  studied at this school before establishing in paris in 1930.
the founder of the school ,  phyllis shillito ,  which opened in 1962 and closed in 1980, firmly believed that `` a student who has mastered the basic principles of design ,  can design anything from a dress to a kitchen stove '' . 
the school existed in three german cities: weimar from 1919 to 1925, dessau from 1925 to 1932, and berlin from 1932 to 1933, under three different architect-directors: walter gropius from 1919 to 1928, hannes meyer from 1928 to 1930, and ludwig mies van der rohe from 1930 until 1933, when the school was closed by its own leadership under pressure from the nazi regime ,  having been painted as a centre of communist intellectualism . 
the vkhutemas ,  the russian state art and technical school founded in 1920 in moscow ,  has been compared to bauhaus . 
