historically ,  the banjo was played in the clawhammer style by the africans who brought their version of the banjo with them . 
modern banjos are typically strung with metal strings . 
open-back banjos generally have a mellower tone and weigh less than resonator banjos . 
these techniques are both idiomatic to the banjo in all styles ,  and their sound is characteristic of bluegrass . 
american old-time music typically uses the five-string ,  open-back banjo . 
several claims as to the etymology of the name `` banjo '' have been made . 
some players may string their banjos with nylon or gut strings to achieve a more mellow ,  old-time tone . 
the five-string banjo has been used in classical music since before the turn of the 20th century . 
they usually have a different setup than a resonator banjo ,  often with a higher string action . 
five-string banjo players use many tunings . 
the first objective of the batting team is to have a player reach first base safely . 
the team that scores the most runs by the end of the game is the winner . 
baseball is a bat-and-ball game played between two opposing teams who take turns batting and fielding . 
a pitch that is not hit into the field of play is called either a strike or a ball . 
a baseball game is played between two teams ,  each composed of nine players ,  that take turns playing offense  -lrb-  batting and baserunning  -rrb-  and defense  -lrb-  pitching and fielding  -rrb-  . 
at the beginning of each half-inning ,  the nine players on the fielding team arrange themselves around the field . 
runners may also attempt to advance to the next base while the pitcher is in the process of delivering the ball to home plate; a successful effort is a stolen base . 
an individual player's turn batting or plate appearance is complete when the player reaches base ,  hits a home run ,  makes an out ,  or hits a ball that results in the team's third out ,  even if it is recorded against a teammate . 
thus ,  even with the dh ,  each team still has a batting order of nine players and a fielding arrangement of nine players . 
several basic offensive tactics come into play with a runner on first base ,  including the fundamental choice of whether to attempt a steal of second base . 
any runners already on base may attempt to advance on batted balls that land ,  or contact the ground ,  in fair territory ,  before or after the ball lands . 
the game is played on a field whose primary boundaries ,  the foul lines ,  extend forward from home plate at 45-degree angles . 
any baseball game involves one or more umpires ,  who make rulings on the outcome of each play . 
stranded runners do not benefit the team in its next turn at bat as every half-inning begins with the bases empty . 
with a runner on third base ,  the infielders may play in ,  moving closer to home plate to improve the odds of throwing out the runner on a ground ball ,  though a sharply hit grounder is more likely to carry through a drawn-in infield . 
baseball has no game clock ,  although most games end in the ninth inning . 
in the playoffs ,  six umpires are used: one at each base and two in the outfield along the foul lines . 
in contrast to many other team sports ,  baseball managers and coaches generally wear their team's uniforms; coaches must be in uniform to be allowed on the field to confer with players during a game . 
