in africa ,  local breeds of sheep may have no mortality ,  but in imported breeds it may be up to 90 percent . 
the two outer capsid proteins ,  vp2 and vp5, mediate attachment and penetration of btv into the target cell . 
in sheep ,  btv causes an acute disease with high morbidity and mortality . 
red deer are an exception ,  and in them the disease may be as acute as in sheep . 
the first confirmed outbreak outside of africa occurred in cyprus in 1943.
a puzzling aspect of btv is its survival between midge seasons in temperate regions . 
nasal signs may be prominent ,  with nasal discharge and stertorous respiration . 
it can kill the horses it infects and mortality may go as high as 90% of the infected horses during an epidemic . 
btv also infects goats ,  cattle and other domestic animals as well as wild ruminants  -lrb-  for example ,  blesbuck ,  white-tailed deer ,  elk ,  and pronghorn antelope  -rrb-  . 
